PN,31907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776380581
OL,3,CWhat a CO2 shortage in the UK means
OL,4,Cfor food, healthcare and hospitality
OL,6,FIt plays an integral part in MRI
OL,7,Fscanning, where it is used to induce
OL,8,Fhypercapnia, which increases blood
OL,9,Fflow to allow clinicians to map brain
OL,10,Fvascular health. The nuclear power
OL,11,Findustry also relies heavily on the
OL,12,Fgas.
OL,14,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,15,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,16,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,17,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,19,FWill there be empty supermarket
OL,20,Fshelves in the UK this summer?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776380581
OL,3,CWhat a CO2 shortage in the UK means
OL,4,Cfor food, healthcare and hospitality
OL,6,FThe war is unlikely to lead to
OL,7,Fcritical shortages, ministers have
OL,8,Fsaid, but there may be less variety on
OL,9,Fthe supermarket shelves should the
OL,10,Fconflict continue in the long term.
OL,12,FWith beer, soft drinks, salad, and
OL,13,Fmeat production affected, a shortage
OL,14,Fcould put a dampener on any summer
OL,15,Fbarbecue plans.
OL,17,FHow is the government planning for a
OL,18,Fshortage?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776380581
OL,3,CWhat a CO2 shortage in the UK means
OL,4,Cfor food, healthcare and hospitality
OL,6,FThe Times reported that officials from
OL,7,FNo 10, the Treasury and the Ministry
OL,8,Fof Defence have taken part in
OL,9,Fscenarios under the codename "Exercise
OL,10,FTurnstone" to work out how to navigate
OL,11,Fa potential CO2 shortage and minimise
OL,12,Fits impact on British industry.
OL,14,FBusiness Secretary Peter Kyle said the
OL,15,Fpublic should be "reassured" by the
OL,16,Fplanning and told Times Radio that
OL,17,Fsupplies of carbon dioxide are "not a
OL,18,Fconcern" for the UK.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1776380581
OL,3,CWhat a CO2 shortage in the UK means
OL,4,Cfor food, healthcare and hospitality
OL,6,FThe business secretary told Sky News
OL,7,Fthere was little cause for concern,
OL,8,Fdespite reports of contingency plans
OL,9,Fin the event of food shortages.
OL,11,F"If any of these things change, I will
OL,12,Fbe up front with the public about it
OL,13,Fin advance so that we can prepare,"
OL,14,FKyle said.
OL,16,F"But right now, people should go on as
OL,17,Fthey are, enjoying beer, enjoying
OL,18,Ftheir meats, enjoying all the salads."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
